The HTML <script> tag
The HTML <script> tag is used to define a client - side script (JavaScript)
The <script> element either contains script statements, or it points to an external script file through
the src attribute
Common uses for JavaScript are image manipulation, form validation, and dynamic changes of
content
To select an hTML element, JavaScript most often uses th document. GetElementById ( ) method
The JavaScript example writes “hello JavaScript!” Into an HTML element with id = “demo”:

