The HTML <noscript> tag
The HTML <noscript> tag defines an alternate content to be displayed to users that have disabled
scripts in their browsers or have a browser that doesn’t support scripts:

So basically:: html and CSS become scripts. And typescript and JavaScript and bootstraps and
panda utilize and bundle these scripts::

<script> defines a client - side script
<noscript> defines an alternate content for users that do not support client side scripts
